1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 11=

3
00:01:38,555 --> 00:01:40,580
I don't have that much time.
I'm very busy.

4
00:01:40,860 --> 00:01:41,740
What you need to do

5
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:43,660
is lay out all the details and pricing

6
00:01:44,140 --> 00:01:46,060
clearly and directly for me.

7
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:47,700
No need for all those packages,

8
00:01:47,860 --> 00:01:49,140
and don't go in circles.

9
00:01:49,340 --> 00:01:51,266
What I want is speed,
the faster the better.

10
00:01:51,660 --> 00:01:52,220
No problem.

11
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:52,980
Mr. Cai,

12
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:54,020
rest assured.

13
00:01:56,100 --> 00:01:56,780
But Mr. Cai,

14
00:01:57,140 --> 00:01:58,060
marriage

15
00:01:58,140 --> 00:01:59,260
is a lifelong matter.

16
00:01:59,340 --> 00:02:00,460
It shouldn't be rushed.

17
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:02,980
It's not my first marriage.

18
00:02:03,060 --> 00:02:04,700
It wasn't this complicated before.

19
00:02:06,666 --> 00:02:08,540
Run the numbers first.
I have a friend coming.

20
00:02:08,977 --> 00:02:09,844
Alright, Mr. Cai.

21
00:02:13,755 --> 00:02:15,200
Ms. Lin, what a coincidence.

22
00:02:15,420 --> 00:02:16,088
You're here too.

23
00:02:17,020 --> 00:02:17,840
(Meant to Be)
What a coincidence.

24
00:02:17,866 --> 00:02:19,911
I just happened to meet a friend here.

25
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:21,822
How has Zhangzhu been lately?

26
00:02:22,220 --> 00:02:23,177
She's doing well.

27
00:02:23,660 --> 00:02:24,940
Eating well, sleeping well,

28
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:26,900
and her work is progressing steadily.

29
00:02:28,620 --> 00:02:29,980
I've been meaning

30
00:02:30,220 --> 00:02:31,500
to ask you to talk to her

31
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:32,580
about attending my wedding.

32
00:02:32,755 --> 00:02:34,020
You see, I'm getting married,

33
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:35,990
and so many friends
from society will be there.

34
00:02:36,244 --> 00:02:37,820
If my own daughter doesn't show up,

35
00:02:38,311 --> 00:02:39,533
it just doesn't look right.

36
00:02:40,133 --> 00:02:41,340
I'll pass along your message

37
00:02:41,340 --> 00:02:42,577
to Zhangzhu when I get back.

38
00:02:42,660 --> 00:02:44,580
But whether she goes or not,

39
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:45,540
you may

40
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:47,620
still have to respect her choice.

41
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:50,300
Ms. Lin,

42
00:02:51,260 --> 00:02:53,460
respect goes both ways.

43
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:54,980
I respect her.

44
00:02:55,420 --> 00:02:56,220
Does she respect me?

45
00:02:57,340 --> 00:02:57,780
Yes,

46
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:00,820
my marriages
have had their ups and downs,

47
00:03:01,266 --> 00:03:02,820
but when it comes to my daughter,

48
00:03:02,820 --> 00:03:04,533
I've always given her
everything she wanted.

49
00:03:04,580 --> 00:03:06,140
I've done my best

50
00:03:06,340 --> 00:03:07,822
to make sure she never suffered.

51
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:10,500
And her mother passed away.

52
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:11,980
We didn't divorce.

53
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:13,740
I didn't abandon her.

54
00:03:14,260 --> 00:03:16,260
And her illness
wasn't caused by me either.

55
00:03:16,580 --> 00:03:17,860
I still have to live my life.

56
00:03:19,060 --> 00:03:20,620
You keep telling her things like

57
00:03:21,820 --> 00:03:22,460
independence,

58
00:03:23,420 --> 00:03:24,380
personality,

59
00:03:24,980 --> 00:03:25,940
and freedom.

60
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:27,500
Don't I also have

61
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:29,060
the right to pursue my own freedom?

62
00:03:30,020 --> 00:03:31,660
When I encounter a new chapter in life,

63
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:33,140
shouldn't she also

64
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:35,222
give me more encouragement and support?

65
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:35,940
Right?

66
00:03:38,060 --> 00:03:40,060
Zhangzhu is already an adult.

67
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:41,700
She's not a child anymore.

68
00:03:42,220 --> 00:03:43,580
She has her own judgment.

69
00:03:44,688 --> 00:03:45,780
This isn't the first time

70
00:03:45,780 --> 00:03:47,355
you've asked her to attend your wedding.

71
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:48,180
Of course,

72
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:49,820
this is the first time she's refused.

73
00:03:50,577 --> 00:03:52,100
She hasn't opposed your remarriage.

74
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:53,220
In a way,

75
00:03:53,580 --> 00:03:54,340
that already shows

76
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:56,500
her support for you

77
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,860
finding a new life.

78
00:03:58,340 --> 00:04:00,644
As for what you said
about independence and freedom,

79
00:04:01,060 --> 00:04:02,380
first you need to distinguish

80
00:04:02,660 --> 00:04:03,780
between your life

81
00:04:04,260 --> 00:04:06,020
and your daughter's life.

82
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:06,780
Right?

83
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:07,580
No matter the age,

84
00:04:08,260 --> 00:04:09,380
basic courtesy

85
00:04:09,620 --> 00:04:11,180
and proper upbringing still matter.

86
00:04:11,420 --> 00:04:13,380
But that doesn't include
being repeatedly forced

87
00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:14,866
to attend her father's weddings,

88
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:16,820
being questioned by other guests

89
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:19,340
about her attitude toward
her new stepmother,

90
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:20,540
and having

91
00:04:20,755 --> 00:04:22,577
to smile and give her blessings

92
00:04:22,780 --> 00:04:24,400
when she clearly doesn't want to.

93
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:26,220
Ms. Lin,

94
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:28,180
have you ever been married?

95
00:04:31,060 --> 00:04:31,420
No.

96
00:04:33,220 --> 00:04:34,660
Then it's hard for you to understand.

97
00:04:36,020 --> 00:04:37,420
You're Zhangzhu's superior.

98
00:04:37,780 --> 00:04:39,260
You seem much older than her,

99
00:04:39,740 --> 00:04:41,340
but both of you are still immature.

100
00:04:42,377 --> 00:04:43,990
You don't understand how the world works

101
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:46,780
or how to handle relationships.

102
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:49,580
If what you call handling relationships

103
00:04:50,180 --> 00:04:52,140
is just repeatedly
getting married and divorced,

104
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:53,900
then I'd rather not understand it.

105
00:04:54,780 --> 00:04:55,180
Mr. Cai,

106
00:04:55,266 --> 00:04:56,377
I've calculated it for you.

107
00:04:56,420 --> 00:04:57,460
Take a look at this figure.

108
00:04:57,470 --> 00:04:58,160
Is it acceptable?

109
00:04:58,180 --> 00:04:59,066
Hold on a moment.

110
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:00,420
Please calm down, Mr. Cai.

111
00:05:00,420 --> 00:05:00,900
Miss Lin.

112
00:05:01,860 --> 00:05:02,300
Miss Lin.

113
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:06,377
My friend is here.

114
00:05:08,660 --> 00:05:09,060
Hello.

115
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:11,580
Hello.

116
00:05:14,980 --> 00:05:15,420
Please sit.

117
00:05:17,180 --> 00:05:17,980
Finally, we meet.

118
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:23,260
Mr. Cai,

119
00:05:23,444 --> 00:05:25,133
is your friend here for a blind date?

120
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:25,980
A blind date?

121
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:28,580
That bracelet she's wearing

122
00:05:28,666 --> 00:05:30,640
is a confirmation token
from a matchmaking platform.

123
00:05:30,660 --> 00:05:31,244
Is that so?

124
00:05:31,940 --> 00:05:34,260
(Meant to Be)

125
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:35,370
And from what I know,

126
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:37,060
that platform is quite well known.

127
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:38,340
And very expensive.

128
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:39,740
Really?

129
00:05:43,022 --> 00:05:44,133
Then I'll head out first.

130
00:05:44,555 --> 00:05:45,733
How are you getting there?

131
00:05:45,844 --> 00:05:47,755
Riding that. Just two
or three kilometers, very close.

132
00:05:47,777 --> 00:05:48,311
What about you?

133
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:49,940
I'm nearby. I'll just walk.

134
00:05:50,380 --> 00:05:51,740
Then let's meet on Wednesday.

135
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:53,133
I'll send you the address later.

136
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:54,460
Alright, that's great.

137
00:05:55,066 --> 00:05:56,020
May I shake your hand?

138
00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:56,780
Of course.

139
00:05:57,444 --> 00:05:58,711
- Nice to meet you.
- Thank you.

140
00:06:02,066 --> 00:06:03,000
See you on Wednesday.

141
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:03,860
Ms. Lin.

142
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:07,860
I wasn't in a good mood just now.

143
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:09,460
I was thinking,

144
00:06:10,044 --> 00:06:11,500
since Zhangzhu
has been staying with you,

145
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:13,066
and you've taken such good care of her,

146
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:14,260
I should thank you.

147
00:06:16,340 --> 00:06:18,020
So about what happened earlier,

148
00:06:18,555 --> 00:06:19,444
I'd like to apologize.

149
00:06:21,780 --> 00:06:22,300
Mr. Cai,

150
00:06:22,860 --> 00:06:23,860
are you always like this,

151
00:06:23,860 --> 00:06:25,666
quick to flare up
and just as quick to cool down?

152
00:06:25,711 --> 00:06:27,020
No, I've just been very busy lately.

153
00:06:27,111 --> 00:06:28,311
It's been frustrating.

154
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:29,740
That person just now...

155
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:31,180
Your blind date?

156
00:06:32,733 --> 00:06:33,755
How did you know?

157
00:06:34,420 --> 00:06:35,260
The bracelet.

158
00:06:35,911 --> 00:06:37,860
Those wedding planners
all know their stuff.

159
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:39,500
That person

160
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:41,333
isn't a good match for you.

161
00:06:43,140 --> 00:06:43,620
Thank you,

162
00:06:44,660 --> 00:06:46,580
but I can judge my own situation.

163
00:06:47,755 --> 00:06:49,380
The best way
to get over one relationship

164
00:06:49,380 --> 00:06:50,660
is to start another one.

165
00:06:51,260 --> 00:06:52,180
But like that just now,

166
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:53,555
it won't help you move on.

167
00:06:53,755 --> 00:06:55,660
It will only make you
miss the past even more.

168
00:06:56,540 --> 00:06:57,340
In this regard,

169
00:06:57,466 --> 00:06:58,340
you can trust me.

170
00:06:58,580 --> 00:07:00,060
I have far more experience than you.

171
00:07:01,511 --> 00:07:02,620
How about I give you a ride?

172
00:07:02,700 --> 00:07:04,300
We can talk more in the car.

173
00:07:06,420 --> 00:07:07,460
I'm really sorry

174
00:07:07,820 --> 00:07:08,700
to trouble you again.

175
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:11,311
Let's talk after you're
done with your work. Goodbye.

176
00:07:12,355 --> 00:07:14,177
Then please help me talk to Zhangzhu.

177
00:07:14,755 --> 00:07:16,666
No matter
how busy things are at the site,

178
00:07:17,340 --> 00:07:19,377
it's nothing compared
to dealing with a woman.

179
00:07:19,977 --> 00:07:21,200
You think it's just

180
00:07:21,288 --> 00:07:23,000
Miss Qian's wedding
that's keeping him busy?

181
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,533
Not even close.

182
00:07:27,020 --> 00:07:28,020
His previous wife...

183
00:07:28,311 --> 00:07:29,660
I can't even remember her name.

184
00:07:31,340 --> 00:07:32,500
Rose, I think.

185
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:34,500
Whether they've been married,

186
00:07:35,340 --> 00:07:36,580
whether they've been divorced,

187
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:38,000
he wants to manage it all.

188
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:43,860
Handling one side,

189
00:07:43,860 --> 00:07:45,940
while eyeing someone new on the other.

190
00:07:46,377 --> 00:07:47,866
Of course, he'd get overwhelmed.

191
00:07:47,940 --> 00:07:49,288
He panics, and then regrets it.

192
00:07:49,844 --> 00:07:52,400
After regretting it, he apologizes,
and it just goes on and on.

193
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:55,155
So you don't go to the wedding?

194
00:08:03,044 --> 00:08:04,660
Your dad is actually pretty good to you.

195
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:05,260
Right?

196
00:08:09,620 --> 00:08:11,311
About as good as he is to other women.

197
00:08:17,860 --> 00:08:19,420
I've already attended two weddings.

198
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:24,460
That's really my limit.

199
00:08:29,355 --> 00:08:31,600
If he gets married again,
I won't go anymore.

200
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:35,620
Can we move on, Boss?

201
00:08:48,644 --> 00:08:49,488
By the way,

202
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:50,940
those five new writers,

203
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:52,755
I didn't get around
to reviewing them earlier

204
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:54,350
because I was dealing
with He Han's comeback

205
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,311
and its impact on Gu Yan.

206
00:08:55,380 --> 00:08:56,750
But I took some time
these past few days,

207
00:08:56,780 --> 00:08:58,044
and they're actually quite good.

208
00:08:58,180 --> 00:08:59,140
In such a short time,

209
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:00,700
being able to pick out these writers

210
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:02,266
shows you really understand the method.

211
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:03,380
Really, Ms. Lin?

212
00:09:03,620 --> 00:09:05,740
You really think all five are good?

213
00:09:06,133 --> 00:09:07,622
Once Zhiyuan Investment funds come in,

214
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:08,980
we can sign new authors.

215
00:09:09,540 --> 00:09:11,333
When that happens,
we'll bring all of them in,

216
00:09:11,377 --> 00:09:12,930
and they'll all
be under your management.

217
00:09:12,940 --> 00:09:13,780
Thank you, Ms. Lin.

218
00:09:15,466 --> 00:09:16,333
By the way,

219
00:09:16,777 --> 00:09:18,000
when you were selecting them,

220
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,377
did you follow any principles?

221
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:34,260
Let me tell you,

222
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:36,844
just remember these three points.

223
00:09:37,460 --> 00:09:38,420
There are

224
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:41,220
three key things.

225
00:09:48,740 --> 00:09:49,780
First...

226
00:09:50,140 --> 00:09:50,580
First,

227
00:09:51,244 --> 00:09:53,355
the most important thing
is the writer's attitude.

228
00:09:53,533 --> 00:09:54,644
They have to be serious.

229
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:56,700
That attitude has to be right.

230
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:00,460
Second...

231
00:10:03,380 --> 00:10:05,500
You must introduce your characters.

232
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,100
Every chapter needs conflict,

233
00:10:07,180 --> 00:10:08,420
every part needs progression,

234
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:09,820
and there must be characters.

235
00:10:10,220 --> 00:10:10,580
Right?

236
00:10:10,666 --> 00:10:11,800
You can't spend forever

237
00:10:11,910 --> 00:10:13,288
building some vague world setting

238
00:10:13,311 --> 00:10:15,530
and not show any characters
within the first two chapters.

239
00:10:15,540 --> 00:10:17,688
Lin Zhanqiao will throw
that straight into the trash.

240
00:10:17,860 --> 00:10:20,100
No empty, overblown setups.

241
00:10:20,555 --> 00:10:21,777
In the opening chapters,

242
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:23,260
your characters must appear.

243
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:25,660
The...

244
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:29,180
The third point...

245
00:10:31,288 --> 00:10:32,711
What is the third point?

246
00:10:37,980 --> 00:10:38,460
Third,

247
00:10:39,420 --> 00:10:40,740
this is Lin Zhanqiao's quirk.

248
00:10:40,888 --> 00:10:42,933
She doesn't like purely
virtuous character types.

249
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:44,620
Your characters

250
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:47,020
can't show up from the start
with a heart of gold.

251
00:10:47,860 --> 00:10:48,300
Why?

252
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:51,900
She thinks it's fake.

253
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:53,700
She can accept

254
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:55,380
a pile of trash

255
00:10:55,980 --> 00:10:57,180
with a bit of gold in it,

256
00:10:57,780 --> 00:10:58,740
but she can't accept

257
00:10:58,820 --> 00:10:59,820
a pile of gold

258
00:10:59,940 --> 00:11:01,340
with even a bit of impurity.

259
00:11:03,460 --> 00:11:04,580
What kind of logic is that?

260
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:06,540
That's why I said it's a quirk.

261
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,420
Lin Zhanqiao has issues with her values.

262
00:11:10,780 --> 00:11:13,140
She doesn't believe
most people are kind and likable.

263
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,740
Unlike me, right?

264
00:11:14,933 --> 00:11:16,066
When I look at people,

265
00:11:16,220 --> 00:11:17,220
especially women,

266
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:19,580
I see every one of them as wonderful.

267
00:11:28,622 --> 00:11:29,888
Is it inconvenient to say?

268
00:11:31,540 --> 00:11:31,900
No.

269
00:11:32,511 --> 00:11:34,140
The third point is that the character

270
00:11:34,820 --> 00:11:36,900
needs flaws and can't be too perfect.

271
00:11:37,733 --> 00:11:38,844
Who taught you that?

272
00:11:43,060 --> 00:11:44,133
Who taught you that?

273
00:11:51,980 --> 00:11:53,060
Don't say it was me.

274
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:02,660
No, I figured it out myself.

275
00:12:04,940 --> 00:12:05,500
I asked

276
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:07,860
Mantou and Fragile

277
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:10,380
for some of the submissions

278
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:13,020
you rated highly
when selecting new writers,

279
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:14,020
and I read all of them.

280
00:12:14,444 --> 00:12:15,088
Ms. Lin.

281
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:19,060
Ms. Lin, you two go ahead.

282
00:12:21,755 --> 00:12:24,200
There's an issue with Zhiyuan
Investment's contract process.

283
00:12:24,220 --> 00:12:24,900
What issue?

284
00:12:25,133 --> 00:12:27,755
They suspect we inflated the data
for our author development program

285
00:12:27,820 --> 00:12:28,580
and want to reassess it.

286
00:12:28,580 --> 00:12:30,340
But we were already
preparing the contracts.

287
00:12:30,540 --> 00:12:31,660
Why would this happen?

288
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:39,660
I'm going to Zhiyuan

289
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:40,900
to see what's going on.

290
00:12:40,955 --> 00:12:41,940
They said they'd give us

291
00:12:41,940 --> 00:12:43,490
a clear explanation
before the end of the day.

292
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:44,466
We can't wait that long.

293
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:52,140
Hello, Mei.

294
00:12:52,222 --> 00:12:53,290
There's a problem with Zhiyuan.

295
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:54,266
I'm heading over now.

296
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:55,644
I'll come find you after work.

297
00:12:56,244 --> 00:12:57,300
I'm already at Zhiyuan.

298
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,450
I just finished talking to them.

299
00:12:58,460 --> 00:12:59,380
I know what's going on.

300
00:12:59,511 --> 00:13:00,320
I'll come find you.

301
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:01,420
Okay, got it.

302
00:13:33,340 --> 00:13:34,380
Why are you at Zhiyuan?

303
00:13:35,140 --> 00:13:36,420
I got the news at 10 AM.

304
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:39,940
Zhiyuan said someone

305
00:13:39,940 --> 00:13:41,288
had already contacted Chenxing.

306
00:13:41,940 --> 00:13:42,820
Who told you?

307
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:44,300
Who else?

308
00:13:45,340 --> 00:13:47,780
If I'm helping, I see it through.

309
00:13:48,177 --> 00:13:49,940
Ever since I helped you
negotiate last time,

310
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:51,160
I've been keeping an eye on it.

311
00:13:51,180 --> 00:13:52,860
No news is good news.

312
00:13:53,244 --> 00:13:54,460
But something came up today,

313
00:13:54,580 --> 00:13:55,740
so I went over immediately.

314
00:13:58,260 --> 00:13:59,020
Mei is in charge,

315
00:13:59,340 --> 00:13:59,860
efficient,

316
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:01,220
just as expected.

317
00:14:01,980 --> 00:14:02,660
Of course.

318
00:14:03,044 --> 00:14:04,260
Otherwise, all these years,

319
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:05,740
with so many people
trying to bring me down,

320
00:14:05,740 --> 00:14:06,711
I wouldn't still be here.

321
00:14:08,140 --> 00:14:08,860
So what exactly

322
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:10,100
did you find out at Zhiyuan?

323
00:14:12,260 --> 00:14:13,060
Zhang Yousen...

324
00:14:13,688 --> 00:14:15,111
Why are you two together?

325
00:14:15,580 --> 00:14:16,555
I asked him to come.

326
00:14:18,980 --> 00:14:21,020
Have all the new author contracts

327
00:14:21,066 --> 00:14:22,644
you reported to Zhiyuan been signed?

328
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:23,740
Not all of them.

329
00:14:25,140 --> 00:14:26,580
Authors are approved one by one,

330
00:14:26,711 --> 00:14:28,400
terms are negotiated one by one,

331
00:14:28,533 --> 00:14:29,490
contracts are processed,

332
00:14:29,540 --> 00:14:30,220
and then signed.

333
00:14:30,980 --> 00:14:32,300
It's impossible for all of them

334
00:14:32,460 --> 00:14:34,177
to be at the same stage
at the same time.

335
00:14:34,422 --> 00:14:36,111
Then for the ones that have been signed,

336
00:14:36,177 --> 00:14:37,311
have they all been paid?

337
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:38,460
Same logic.

338
00:14:38,733 --> 00:14:40,311
What percentage has been paid?

339
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:41,900
Some of them.

340
00:14:46,380 --> 00:14:47,340
I did plan

341
00:14:48,420 --> 00:14:49,740
to use Zhiyuan Investment's funds

342
00:14:50,580 --> 00:14:52,180
to pay most of the authors' deposits.

343
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:55,740
And I stated it very clearly

344
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:56,860
in the financing report.

345
00:14:57,380 --> 00:14:59,010
Most of the financing would be used

346
00:14:59,010 --> 00:15:01,020
to develop and discover new authors.

347
00:15:01,340 --> 00:15:02,740
That depends on the terms

348
00:15:03,288 --> 00:15:04,977
you negotiated with the new authors.

349
00:15:05,140 --> 00:15:05,980
Generally speaking,

350
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:07,540
if the contract only takes effect

351
00:15:07,860 --> 00:15:09,180
after payment,

352
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:10,622
then right now,

353
00:15:10,644 --> 00:15:12,660
performance of the contract
hasn't started yet.

354
00:15:14,140 --> 00:15:15,100
Sir, your water.

355
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:15,740
Thank you.

356
00:15:17,540 --> 00:15:19,020
In cases like this,

357
00:15:19,822 --> 00:15:21,355
there is usually a whistleblower.

358
00:15:21,933 --> 00:15:23,155
A whistleblower for what?

359
00:15:25,222 --> 00:15:26,666
Zhiyuan Investment has never

360
00:15:26,755 --> 00:15:28,940
raised any doubts
about these issues before.

361
00:15:30,380 --> 00:15:32,620
And they've seen our
communication progress

362
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:34,580
with the authors

363
00:15:34,644 --> 00:15:36,100
and all copies of the contracts.

364
00:15:36,340 --> 00:15:37,380
Then, is it possible

365
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,180
to pay all the deposits

366
00:15:39,460 --> 00:15:40,180
we can now?

367
00:15:40,820 --> 00:15:43,060
As for the rest that are still
going through the process,

368
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:45,444
we may need
to make some changes there too.

369
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:51,300
If we pay everything now,

370
00:15:52,888 --> 00:15:55,177
the company really doesn't
have that much money.

371
00:15:56,300 --> 00:15:57,460
Pay as much as we can.

372
00:15:59,180 --> 00:16:00,980
If I pay all this money out,

373
00:16:02,488 --> 00:16:03,644
and Zhiyuan Investment

374
00:16:03,688 --> 00:16:05,200
withdraws its investment in me,

375
00:16:05,780 --> 00:16:07,860
then I won't have money
left for anything else.

376
00:16:10,860 --> 00:16:11,460
Rent,

377
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:13,466
and staff salaries...

378
00:16:15,733 --> 00:16:17,222
I won't be able to cover them.

379
00:16:22,020 --> 00:16:23,220
I have another concern.

380
00:16:23,733 --> 00:16:26,066
Could the news have reached Zhiyuan
because some authors

381
00:16:26,580 --> 00:16:27,860
have already walked away?

382
00:16:37,911 --> 00:16:39,320
The three of us
contacted them separately.

383
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:40,810
Fragile and I each
made more than a dozen calls.

384
00:16:40,810 --> 00:16:41,500
Zhangzhu was still in charge of

385
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,800
the five new authors from before.

386
00:16:42,820 --> 00:16:43,340
Results?

387
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:44,540
I made twelve calls.

388
00:16:44,540 --> 00:16:45,460
Seven are in the contract process.

389
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:46,220
One has already been paid.

390
00:16:46,220 --> 00:16:48,300
The remaining four have signed
but haven't been paid yet.

391
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:49,860
Of those,
two didn't answer their phones.

392
00:16:49,860 --> 00:16:51,140
One is waiting for our payment.

393
00:16:51,140 --> 00:16:52,488
And the last one clearly said

394
00:16:52,711 --> 00:16:54,660
they won't work with us anymore.

395
00:16:54,733 --> 00:16:56,977
If they're not working with us,
who are they working with?

396
00:16:57,580 --> 00:16:58,580
It's...

397
00:17:00,740 --> 00:17:02,300
Ms. Lin, I contacted ten people.

398
00:17:02,620 --> 00:17:04,260
I think we've lost three new authors.

399
00:17:04,460 --> 00:17:05,780
Other companies got to them first.

400
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:06,420
Three?

401
00:17:08,740 --> 00:17:09,180
Ms. Lin.

402
00:17:09,420 --> 00:17:10,060
Don't rush.

403
00:17:10,711 --> 00:17:11,488
Take your time.

404
00:17:12,060 --> 00:17:12,700
All five of them

405
00:17:13,140 --> 00:17:13,900
left together.

406
00:17:16,733 --> 00:17:17,644
What do you mean?

407
00:17:18,111 --> 00:17:20,140
He said they don't want
to work with us anymore.

408
00:17:20,260 --> 00:17:20,940
The reason?

409
00:17:21,380 --> 00:17:22,740
Other companies approached them.

410
00:17:24,340 --> 00:17:24,940
They...

411
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:31,180
The five of them

412
00:17:31,180 --> 00:17:32,260
don't even know each other,

413
00:17:32,260 --> 00:17:33,780
and they're not even in the same city.

414
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:37,300
Someone managed
to reach all five of them.

415
00:17:42,420 --> 00:17:43,060
Zhangzhu,

416
00:17:43,422 --> 00:17:45,622
you know that this kind
of author information

417
00:17:45,644 --> 00:17:46,911
must be kept confidential, right?

418
00:17:47,020 --> 00:17:48,500
Of course. Ms. Lin told me that.

419
00:17:50,340 --> 00:17:50,900
I swear,

420
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:53,020
I never let their information
leave this office.

421
00:17:54,980 --> 00:17:56,540
Do we know which company they went to?

422
00:17:56,780 --> 00:17:57,890
I asked, but they wouldn't say.

423
00:17:57,940 --> 00:17:58,911
Find out immediately.

424
00:18:09,422 --> 00:18:11,240
(When problems
keep coming one after another,)

425
00:18:11,740 --> 00:18:12,500
(there's no time)

426
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:14,180
(for frustration or regret to grow.)

427
00:18:15,222 --> 00:18:16,422
(The only way forward)

428
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:18,540
(is to deal with each one calmly,)

429
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:20,333
(pressing on until you're exhausted,)

430
00:18:20,488 --> 00:18:21,822
(either solving the trouble,)

431
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:23,300
(or being consumed by it.)

432
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:57,220
(Find a nice place tonight.
Buy me a drink.)

433
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:04,140
(Deal.)

434
00:20:01,460 --> 00:20:02,100
Wait for me.

435
00:20:03,540 --> 00:20:04,380
Just leave it here.

436
00:20:04,700 --> 00:20:05,140
Thanks.

437
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:08,860
Mr. Ling.

438
00:20:09,140 --> 00:20:09,500
Mr. Ling.

439
00:20:11,755 --> 00:20:12,711
What's going on?

440
00:20:13,340 --> 00:20:14,100
Moving offices.

441
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:15,955
Wasn't the previous one fine?

442
00:20:16,688 --> 00:20:19,311
The feng shui master said having
no backing behind me is bad.

443
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:20,820
This room suits me better.

444
00:20:21,022 --> 00:20:22,933
What, are you saving
the other one for someone?

445
00:20:23,340 --> 00:20:23,780
No.

446
00:20:26,980 --> 00:20:28,460
That office was too far from you.

447
00:20:28,666 --> 00:20:29,933
This one is right next to yours.

448
00:20:30,022 --> 00:20:30,720
More convenient.

449
00:20:36,220 --> 00:20:37,400
You sold the apartment?

450
00:20:37,860 --> 00:20:39,822
I told you I could raise
at least seven million.

451
00:20:39,940 --> 00:20:40,860
I wasn't joking.

452
00:20:41,660 --> 00:20:42,980
You said this is our company.

453
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:44,900
I hope you're not joking either.

454
00:20:47,780 --> 00:20:48,466
Don't worry.

455
00:20:48,700 --> 00:20:50,400
I'll use the money where it matters.

456
00:20:53,020 --> 00:20:53,620
After work,

457
00:20:53,620 --> 00:20:55,355
come over to my new place for dinner.

458
00:20:56,777 --> 00:20:58,420
Money's tight during this startup phase,

459
00:20:58,420 --> 00:20:59,822
so I couldn't get a great place,

460
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:01,340
but I think you'll like it.

461
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:06,844
You'll see when you come.

462
00:21:43,020 --> 00:21:46,300
(I'm starving. Come early. Can't wait.)

463
00:21:48,460 --> 00:21:50,460
(As soon as possible.)

464
00:21:55,820 --> 00:21:57,100
Gu Yan's update just came in.

465
00:22:00,311 --> 00:22:02,377
Good thing you reminded me.
I almost forgot.

466
00:22:02,740 --> 00:22:03,220
Zhangzhu.

467
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:05,860
Ms. Lin.

468
00:22:06,740 --> 00:22:07,620
Let Gu Yan know

469
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:10,300
there's something urgent at the company.

470
00:22:10,860 --> 00:22:11,940
I'll contact him tonight.

471
00:22:12,340 --> 00:22:12,660
Got it.

472
00:22:13,020 --> 00:22:13,900
I'm heading out now.

473
00:22:14,111 --> 00:22:15,377
Call me if anything comes up.

474
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:15,860
Okay.

475
00:22:45,780 --> 00:22:46,180
Hello.

476
00:22:47,860 --> 00:22:48,540
I'm on the way.

477
00:22:48,660 --> 00:22:49,577
I'll be there soon.

478
00:22:50,580 --> 00:22:51,300
Alright, see you.

479
00:23:36,980 --> 00:23:38,020
What took you so long?

480
00:23:38,620 --> 00:23:39,220
Sorry.

481
00:23:39,500 --> 00:23:40,780
Something urgent came up.

482
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:42,140
I almost couldn't make it.

483
00:23:43,860 --> 00:23:45,311
If no one's dead, it's not urgent.

484
00:23:46,540 --> 00:23:47,340
When did you arrive?

485
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:48,711
A couple of days ago.

486
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:49,740
I've already ordered.

487
00:23:49,910 --> 00:23:51,044
You can add more if you want.

488
00:23:51,088 --> 00:23:51,800
Excuse me.

489
00:23:52,755 --> 00:23:53,977
Could we order, please?

490
00:23:57,133 --> 00:23:58,200
Alright, thank you.

491
00:23:58,580 --> 00:23:59,540
A vegetable salad,

492
00:23:59,900 --> 00:24:01,660
and a room temperature soda. Thank you.

493
00:24:01,780 --> 00:24:02,100
Wait.

494
00:24:02,660 --> 00:24:03,700
You're not getting a drink?

495
00:24:04,060 --> 00:24:04,940
I'll pass.

496
00:24:04,940 --> 00:24:06,580
I still have work to deal with later.

497
00:24:07,180 --> 00:24:07,940
One drink

498
00:24:07,940 --> 00:24:09,260
won't delay your work.

499
00:24:09,580 --> 00:24:10,180
If you

500
00:24:11,180 --> 00:24:12,500
can't handle it,

501
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:14,466
you won't handle it
even without drinking.

502
00:24:14,555 --> 00:24:15,580
Here. Get her a drink, too.

503
00:24:15,700 --> 00:24:16,420
Same with me.

504
00:24:24,180 --> 00:24:24,900
Okay. That's all.

505
00:24:25,540 --> 00:24:25,940
Thank you.

506
00:24:26,555 --> 00:24:27,866
Just leave the decanter here.

507
00:24:28,140 --> 00:24:28,580
Enjoy.

508
00:24:33,100 --> 00:24:34,980
I haven't even had lunch yet.

509
00:24:35,660 --> 00:24:36,380
At that hotel,

510
00:24:36,511 --> 00:24:37,800
everything is so expensive.

511
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:40,540
That little rascal
made me pay for everything.

512
00:24:40,955 --> 00:24:42,711
Don't you think he's heartless?

513
00:24:42,911 --> 00:24:44,311
Doesn't that count as elder abuse?

514
00:24:45,740 --> 00:24:47,020
Why did you suddenly come here?

515
00:24:51,420 --> 00:24:53,220
I moved into a retirement home.

516
00:24:59,660 --> 00:25:00,060
You...

517
00:25:00,580 --> 00:25:02,340
When you get the chance,

518
00:25:03,020 --> 00:25:05,460
come visit me once a month, alright?

519
00:25:06,580 --> 00:25:07,980
Bring me something from Shanghai.

520
00:25:16,220 --> 00:25:16,980
Does He Han know?

521
00:25:17,820 --> 00:25:18,380
He does.

522
00:25:19,620 --> 00:25:20,380
You know how it is.

523
00:25:20,844 --> 00:25:22,000
Between him and me,

524
00:25:22,688 --> 00:25:23,888
out of sight, out of mind.

525
00:25:26,140 --> 00:25:26,580
Hello,

526
00:25:26,780 --> 00:25:27,460
your dishes.

527
00:25:32,260 --> 00:25:33,420
Time to eat.

528
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:35,620
Tomahawk steak.

529
00:25:37,420 --> 00:25:38,311
You ordered this?

530
00:25:39,740 --> 00:25:40,620
You're paying,

531
00:25:40,740 --> 00:25:41,540
so I'll eat more.

532
00:25:42,888 --> 00:25:44,180
Once I'm in the retirement home,

533
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:45,555
I won't get to eat this anymore.

534
00:25:47,140 --> 00:25:48,100
It's fine to eat.

535
00:25:48,180 --> 00:25:49,340
Just don't overdo it.

536
00:25:50,020 --> 00:25:50,730
Too much

537
00:25:50,730 --> 00:25:51,620
is hard to digest.

538
00:25:51,860 --> 00:25:53,377
If it's hard to digest, that's fine.

539
00:25:54,340 --> 00:25:55,740
Drink more wine and it'll go down.

540
00:25:57,060 --> 00:25:57,380
Here.

541
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:00,980
This drink is for you,

542
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:02,800
for getting out of that mess.

543
00:26:05,540 --> 00:26:06,540
What mess?

544
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:08,511
You broke up with that rascal.

545
00:26:09,780 --> 00:26:10,490
He's the type

546
00:26:10,490 --> 00:26:11,844
who never lasts with anyone.

547
00:26:12,860 --> 00:26:13,500
Before,

548
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:15,540
every time I saw you, I warned you

549
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:17,860
not to be fooled
by his outward appearance.

550
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:18,933
You wouldn't listen.

551
00:26:20,111 --> 00:26:22,511
If things were good for a while,
fine, let them be.

552
00:26:23,022 --> 00:26:25,355
But if you thought you
could turn something temporary

553
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,777
into something lasting,

554
00:26:27,377 --> 00:26:28,577
then you're finished.

555
00:26:28,700 --> 00:26:30,622
You wouldn't even know
how you lost everything.

556
00:26:31,700 --> 00:26:32,860
Now I know.

557
00:26:36,066 --> 00:26:37,777
The moment he broke up with you,

558
00:26:38,177 --> 00:26:39,066
look at that,

559
00:26:39,755 --> 00:26:41,466
he immediately found someone else.

560
00:26:42,860 --> 00:26:43,650
Before,

561
00:26:43,650 --> 00:26:45,500
he always went for younger ones.

562
00:26:45,980 --> 00:26:47,180
When you were with him,

563
00:26:47,180 --> 00:26:48,777
you weren't that old either, right?

564
00:26:48,933 --> 00:26:50,777
This time, who knows what he's thinking,

565
00:26:50,977 --> 00:26:52,244
he found someone older.

566
00:26:53,060 --> 00:26:53,700
This won't work.

567
00:26:56,260 --> 00:26:57,660
Otherwise I wouldn't have asked you

568
00:26:57,980 --> 00:26:59,022
to come drink with me.

569
00:27:01,740 --> 00:27:02,460
What do you mean?

570
00:27:34,140 --> 00:27:34,940
Who are you?

571
00:27:38,860 --> 00:27:39,380
Who are you?

572
00:27:40,980 --> 00:27:42,060
You're Uncle He, right?

573
00:27:43,460 --> 00:27:44,300
My name is Dai Shan.

574
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:46,780
I'm He Han's agent and editor.

575
00:27:49,220 --> 00:27:50,580
He's inside?

576
00:27:52,060 --> 00:27:52,780
I'll go get him?

577
00:27:53,460 --> 00:27:53,900
No.

578
00:27:56,340 --> 00:27:57,020
Come.

579
00:28:02,980 --> 00:28:03,940
Let's not disturb him.

580
00:28:04,460 --> 00:28:05,133
How about this?

581
00:28:05,740 --> 00:28:06,900
Down in the lobby,

582
00:28:07,860 --> 00:28:08,500
at the bar,

583
00:28:08,900 --> 00:28:09,660
buy me a drink,

584
00:28:10,420 --> 00:28:11,540
and I'll tell you

585
00:28:12,180 --> 00:28:13,100
his whole story

586
00:28:13,260 --> 00:28:13,780
growing up.

587
00:28:14,900 --> 00:28:16,180
I'm not interested

588
00:28:16,260 --> 00:28:17,220
in his life story.

589
00:28:18,020 --> 00:28:20,140
Then you won't be able

590
00:28:20,222 --> 00:28:21,755
to understand him at the root.

591
00:28:21,900 --> 00:28:24,100
I'm only interested
in how much money he makes.

592
00:28:24,620 --> 00:28:25,460
Money matters,

593
00:28:25,460 --> 00:28:27,066
but where he comes from matters too.

594
00:28:27,260 --> 00:28:28,860
People say, you can tell a lot

595
00:28:28,980 --> 00:28:30,288
about someone from a young age.

596
00:28:30,488 --> 00:28:31,666
Not even that young.

597
00:28:31,980 --> 00:28:32,940
When he was eight,

598
00:28:33,140 --> 00:28:34,100
something happened.

599
00:28:34,940 --> 00:28:36,900
That one incident

600
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,444
set the tone for his whole life.

601
00:28:39,940 --> 00:28:41,660
Want to know what it was?

602
00:28:42,866 --> 00:28:43,500
Have a drink.

603
00:28:45,140 --> 00:28:45,900
Not interested.

604
00:28:45,980 --> 00:28:46,540
Sorry.

605
00:28:50,340 --> 00:28:51,700
So what was it?

606
00:28:52,044 --> 00:28:53,355
What do you mean what?

607
00:28:53,540 --> 00:28:55,260
That thing when he was eight.

608
00:28:57,311 --> 00:28:58,666
I haven't thought it through yet.

609
00:29:00,755 --> 00:29:02,260
If she won't buy me a drink,

610
00:29:02,260 --> 00:29:03,610
then I won't bother making it up.

611
00:29:05,340 --> 00:29:07,180
So all those stories

612
00:29:07,180 --> 00:29:08,220
you told me before,

613
00:29:08,300 --> 00:29:09,180
they were all made up?

614
00:29:11,020 --> 00:29:11,620
Not entirely.

615
00:29:13,420 --> 00:29:14,180
Now I see

616
00:29:14,180 --> 00:29:15,660
why He Han writes novels.

617
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:20,940
Even if they're made up,

618
00:29:21,155 --> 00:29:22,822
there's always some truth behind them.

619
00:29:23,100 --> 00:29:23,860
You know that.

620
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,555
No matter how you dress it up,

621
00:29:26,820 --> 00:29:27,780
a jerk is still a jerk.

622
00:29:28,580 --> 00:29:30,460
That part is absolutely true.

623
00:29:42,220 --> 00:29:42,580
This way.

624
00:29:53,977 --> 00:29:55,022
Turn left here.

625
00:30:16,088 --> 00:30:17,355
Why rent a place here?

626
00:30:18,177 --> 00:30:20,777
With this budget,
you can't get anything good anywhere.

627
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:22,911
Might as well pick somewhere meaningful.

628
00:30:23,066 --> 00:30:24,466
What's meaningful about this place?

629
00:30:24,860 --> 00:30:25,780
It's where you grew up.

630
00:30:27,340 --> 00:30:28,860
I want to know how you grew up,

631
00:30:29,177 --> 00:30:30,880
and what drove you
to push yourself so hard.

632
00:30:31,140 --> 00:30:32,340
Is it the same reason as me?

633
00:30:36,333 --> 00:30:38,022
Your grandmother still lives here.

634
00:30:38,300 --> 00:30:39,711
I can go visit her for you.

635
00:30:55,740 --> 00:30:56,980
When you visit her,

636
00:30:57,777 --> 00:30:59,088
don't move things around.

637
00:31:01,060 --> 00:31:02,500
Her eyesight isn't good anymore.

638
00:31:03,740 --> 00:31:04,460
Everything

639
00:31:05,500 --> 00:31:06,660
has to stay in its place.

640
00:31:08,022 --> 00:31:09,911
Didn't you hire
someone to take care of her?

641
00:31:09,980 --> 00:31:10,580
I did.

642
00:31:14,066 --> 00:31:15,466
There's a caretaker during the day,

643
00:31:15,533 --> 00:31:17,555
but grandmother
won't turn on the lights at night.

644
00:31:18,022 --> 00:31:19,266
The caretakers can't stand it,

645
00:31:19,555 --> 00:31:20,622
and they don't stay.

646
00:31:32,977 --> 00:31:34,755
Can you really get used
to living like this?

647
00:31:36,060 --> 00:31:37,860
This kind of hardship is nothing to me.

648
00:31:38,940 --> 00:31:40,260
As long as I know my goal,

649
00:31:40,900 --> 00:31:41,780
I can endure it.

650
00:31:43,500 --> 00:31:44,660
I really don't understand you.

651
00:31:45,580 --> 00:31:46,580
I've told you before.

652
00:31:49,044 --> 00:31:50,355
Then I'll say it again.

653
00:31:51,933 --> 00:31:53,355
I want Colorful Culture Media

654
00:31:53,377 --> 00:31:54,822
to have a place in the industry.

655
00:31:55,140 --> 00:31:56,220
I want you and me

656
00:31:56,780 --> 00:31:58,220
to become leaders in this field.

657
00:32:01,260 --> 00:32:03,300
Before, it was Lin Zhanqiao and He Han.

658
00:32:03,888 --> 00:32:06,288
In the future,
it will be Zhao Lanxin and Ling Yikai.

659
00:32:08,260 --> 00:32:10,300
You fought your way up from the slums.

660
00:32:11,540 --> 00:32:12,820
Top middle school,

661
00:32:13,300 --> 00:32:14,380
top university,

662
00:32:15,311 --> 00:32:17,333
and now you've started your own company.

663
00:32:18,244 --> 00:32:19,400
You've worked this hard

664
00:32:20,460 --> 00:32:22,100
just to be seen, right?

665
00:32:24,860 --> 00:32:25,940
We're the same.

666
00:32:28,977 --> 00:32:30,066
What are you doing?

667
00:32:33,500 --> 00:32:34,660
You planned all this,

668
00:32:35,980 --> 00:32:36,660
brought me here,

669
00:32:38,740 --> 00:32:39,780
just to say these things?

670
00:32:42,740 --> 00:32:43,580
Did it work?

671
00:32:56,540 --> 00:32:57,420
Last drink.

672
00:33:02,180 --> 00:33:03,580
Tell me,

673
00:33:05,220 --> 00:33:06,420
a person who loves drinking

674
00:33:07,740 --> 00:33:09,220
but never gets drunk.

675
00:33:11,140 --> 00:33:12,540
Doesn't that sound contradictory?

676
00:33:15,140 --> 00:33:16,260
Do you know why

677
00:33:16,860 --> 00:33:17,580
I was so good

678
00:33:17,580 --> 00:33:19,380
at selling machines back then?

679
00:33:20,300 --> 00:33:22,740
Because I never got drunk.

680
00:33:22,866 --> 00:33:23,820
If they wouldn't pay,

681
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:25,859
I'd grab a bottle of aged liquor

682
00:33:25,860 --> 00:33:27,377
and down it right in front of them.

683
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:28,720
Then they would sign on the spot.

684
00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:30,740
And I even had to pretend to be drunk.

685
00:33:34,022 --> 00:33:35,888
Heavy drinking runs in the family.

686
00:33:40,340 --> 00:33:41,140
He Han?

687
00:33:42,088 --> 00:33:43,088
He can't do it.

688
00:33:43,533 --> 00:33:44,777
He doesn't have it in him.

689
00:33:46,660 --> 00:33:48,460
Two drinks and his hands start shaking.

690
00:33:48,660 --> 00:33:50,860
One more sip
and his whole body trembles.

691
00:33:51,133 --> 00:33:52,622
What kind of problem is that?

692
00:33:54,820 --> 00:33:56,100
Someone who loves drinking

693
00:33:58,380 --> 00:33:59,580
can't handle alcohol?

694
00:34:02,100 --> 00:34:02,820
That's a curse.

695
00:34:05,740 --> 00:34:07,260
It's punishment from heaven.

696
00:34:12,333 --> 00:34:14,422
If he doesn't drink, he feels miserable.

697
00:34:15,222 --> 00:34:16,888
If he drinks, he's ruining himself.

698
00:34:18,977 --> 00:34:20,844
If that's not a curse, what is?

699
00:34:34,660 --> 00:34:36,100
He Wei, dinner's ready.

700
00:34:54,860 --> 00:34:55,740
Your phone is ringing.

701
00:35:02,980 --> 00:35:03,260
Hello?

702
00:35:03,660 --> 00:35:04,220
Where are you?

703
00:35:05,940 --> 00:35:06,980
Zhanqiao is treating me

704
00:35:07,340 --> 00:35:08,140
to steak.

705
00:35:09,060 --> 00:35:09,820
Tomahawk.

706
00:35:25,300 --> 00:35:25,900
I'm sorry.

707
00:35:26,355 --> 00:35:27,688
Please help me get him back.

708
00:36:28,980 --> 00:36:30,420
You've been drinking a lot lately.

709
00:36:31,511 --> 00:36:33,022
Too many happy occasions.

710
00:36:33,580 --> 00:36:33,900
Right.

711
00:36:34,420 --> 00:36:35,822
Happy occasions call for drinks.

712
00:36:51,580 --> 00:36:52,220
Don't think

713
00:36:53,260 --> 00:36:55,340
I'm just some failure.

714
00:36:57,580 --> 00:36:59,380
He Han writes well now

715
00:37:00,066 --> 00:37:01,355
and makes good money.

716
00:37:01,420 --> 00:37:02,460
He should thank me.

717
00:37:02,700 --> 00:37:03,580
No pain,

718
00:37:04,220 --> 00:37:05,180
no gain.

719
00:37:05,980 --> 00:37:07,500
I gave him life experience.

720
00:37:09,220 --> 00:37:11,020
A kid raised in comfort

721
00:37:11,422 --> 00:37:13,577
would never understand
bitterness and hardship.

722
00:37:14,933 --> 00:37:16,200
So when it comes to many things,

723
00:37:16,300 --> 00:37:17,866
you can't just look at one side.

724
00:37:20,860 --> 00:37:21,780
Have you ever thought

725
00:37:23,177 --> 00:37:25,222
that he might rather not
have all this money,

726
00:37:26,100 --> 00:37:26,940
if he could

727
00:37:27,580 --> 00:37:28,820
erase all the pain

728
00:37:28,820 --> 00:37:30,260
you put him through?

729
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,460
Now that he has money,

730
00:37:33,460 --> 00:37:34,500
of course, he'd say that.

731
00:37:35,460 --> 00:37:36,220
If he didn't,

732
00:37:36,444 --> 00:37:37,955
you'd see what he'd say then.

733
00:37:41,100 --> 00:37:41,820
People...

734
00:37:43,060 --> 00:37:44,340
are born to suffer.

735
00:37:46,500 --> 00:37:47,940
If it's not one kind, it's another.

736
00:37:49,488 --> 00:37:51,810
That bit of hardship he went through,
you call that suffering?

737
00:37:51,822 --> 00:37:52,733
That's what you call

738
00:37:54,140 --> 00:37:54,820
experience.

739
00:37:55,740 --> 00:37:56,180
Right?

740
00:37:57,260 --> 00:37:59,140
But you almost got him killed.

741
00:37:59,644 --> 00:38:01,044
He smashed my wine bottle.

742
00:38:01,111 --> 00:38:02,555
I hit him, and he deserved it.

743
00:38:03,555 --> 00:38:04,980
Why couldn't he just talk things out?

744
00:38:04,980 --> 00:38:06,111
Why grab the bottle?

745
00:38:06,488 --> 00:38:07,740
A whole bottle of fine liquor,

746
00:38:07,822 --> 00:38:09,244
and he smashed it on the ground.

747
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:11,540
He fell

748
00:38:11,620 --> 00:38:13,060
and hit the broken glass himself.

749
00:38:13,700 --> 00:38:15,660
If I hadn't gotten him
to the hospital in time,

750
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:16,977
he would have gone blind.

751
00:38:21,300 --> 00:38:22,180
You try it.

752
00:38:22,180 --> 00:38:23,540
Go grab his bottle now.

753
00:38:23,666 --> 00:38:25,020
See if he slaps you or not.

754
00:38:44,220 --> 00:38:44,660
Alright.

755
00:38:44,780 --> 00:38:46,266
You should head back and rest.

756
00:38:46,280 --> 00:38:47,660
It's fine. I'll walk you upstairs.

757
00:38:47,660 --> 00:38:48,380
No need.

758
00:38:49,300 --> 00:38:50,860
It's late. A woman following me up...

759
00:38:51,088 --> 00:38:52,900
People will think
I picked you up at a bar.

760
00:38:52,900 --> 00:38:53,940
It's fine.

761
00:38:55,460 --> 00:38:56,540
Let him go up on his own.

762
00:38:58,860 --> 00:38:59,540
How much was it?

763
00:38:59,740 --> 00:39:00,822
I'll transfer it to you.

764
00:39:01,380 --> 00:39:01,940
Two thousand.

765
00:39:03,180 --> 00:39:04,220
Lin Zhanqiao treated me.

766
00:39:04,580 --> 00:39:05,140
It was free.

767
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:06,140
No need to pay.

768
00:39:08,780 --> 00:39:09,460
See?

769
00:39:09,540 --> 00:39:11,180
Meals are meant to be paid for.

770
00:39:14,940 --> 00:39:15,460
Zhanqiao,

771
00:39:16,180 --> 00:39:17,060
you've become stingy.

772
00:39:17,088 --> 00:39:18,533
If he comes looking for you again,

773
00:39:18,577 --> 00:39:20,000
just say you're busy. Ignore him.

774
00:39:28,500 --> 00:39:28,940
Thanks.

775
00:39:32,900 --> 00:39:33,980
Your dad suddenly came here

776
00:39:34,340 --> 00:39:35,466
and asked me to dinner.

777
00:39:35,577 --> 00:39:37,266
He probably has something in mind.

778
00:39:40,100 --> 00:39:40,540
Got it.

779
00:39:41,460 --> 00:39:42,340
Also, don't hide it.

780
00:39:45,140 --> 00:39:45,900
If you drink later,

781
00:39:46,100 --> 00:39:47,622
you two will end up arguing again.

782
00:39:48,340 --> 00:39:48,900
Don't worry.

783
00:39:49,088 --> 00:39:50,200
I know what I'm doing.

784
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:13,911
Now this is great.

785
00:40:14,577 --> 00:40:16,777
Zhiyuan Investment
has stopped funding Chenxing.

786
00:40:17,420 --> 00:40:18,540
What about our new authors?

787
00:40:18,644 --> 00:40:20,822
Why do you think
I asked you to raise seven million?

788
00:40:21,180 --> 00:40:22,260
Strike first.

789
00:40:22,622 --> 00:40:23,580
It's all been paid out?

790
00:40:23,700 --> 00:40:24,100
Of course.

791
00:40:25,900 --> 00:40:26,420
How many?

792
00:40:26,580 --> 00:40:27,140
Five.

793
00:40:27,222 --> 00:40:28,777
The rest are still in progress.

794
00:40:30,100 --> 00:40:31,540
Pay first, and handle things later.

795
00:40:31,933 --> 00:40:33,860
Looks like for new authors,
the biggest concern

796
00:40:33,980 --> 00:40:35,780
is how quickly they can get paid.

797
00:40:35,980 --> 00:40:36,930
In the end, where did

798
00:40:36,930 --> 00:40:38,866
Lin Zhanqiao's funding
from Zhiyuan come from?

799
00:40:38,955 --> 00:40:40,511
Taken from what should have gone to us.

800
00:40:40,660 --> 00:40:42,000
If we can't get it, how can she?

801
00:40:45,955 --> 00:40:47,220
Then we take Lin Zhanqiao down.

802
00:40:47,220 --> 00:40:48,260
First, leverage Mr. Fan.

803
00:40:49,420 --> 00:40:50,380
We're going to build

804
00:40:51,060 --> 00:40:51,780
the largest

805
00:40:51,900 --> 00:40:53,180
web fiction content supplier.

806
00:40:53,660 --> 00:40:54,940
Set up training, build a school,

807
00:40:54,940 --> 00:40:56,260
and create our own platform.

808
00:40:56,740 --> 00:40:57,740
Then replace Mr. Fan.

809
00:40:57,900 --> 00:40:59,100
Seven years... Is that enough?

810
00:41:00,466 --> 00:41:02,000
Do we have that kind of patience?

811
00:41:02,340 --> 00:41:02,900
Five years.

812
00:41:03,460 --> 00:41:03,980
Three years.

813
00:41:37,140 --> 00:41:37,740
Ms. Lin,

814
00:41:38,980 --> 00:41:40,940
the new authors I found

815
00:41:41,900 --> 00:41:43,140
have all been poached.

816
00:41:47,500 --> 00:41:48,020
By who?

817
00:41:49,740 --> 00:41:51,420
Let her calm down first.

818
00:41:54,620 --> 00:41:55,540
Colorful Culture Media?

819
00:41:57,333 --> 00:41:58,955
They've already signed them.

820
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:00,377
All five of them are signed.

821
00:42:00,540 --> 00:42:01,780
They must have offered

822
00:42:01,933 --> 00:42:03,244
more money than we did.

823
00:42:12,380 --> 00:42:13,860
What about

824
00:42:14,500 --> 00:42:15,140
the others?

825
00:42:15,900 --> 00:42:16,660
Not sure yet.

826
00:42:17,155 --> 00:42:18,155
But these ones...

827
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:19,711
Because they hadn't signed with us yet,

828
00:42:19,733 --> 00:42:21,980
they went ahead and signed
with Colorful Culture Media,

829
00:42:21,980 --> 00:42:22,820
and word got out.

830
00:42:24,060 --> 00:42:25,660
Aren't they worried about disputes?

831
00:42:25,860 --> 00:42:26,820
There's an insider

832
00:42:26,900 --> 00:42:27,580
in your company.

833
00:42:29,220 --> 00:42:30,940
It's not me, really not.

834
00:42:31,180 --> 00:42:33,140
I found all these authors myself.

835
00:42:33,140 --> 00:42:35,140
I wouldn't sabotage my own work.

836
00:42:36,022 --> 00:42:37,866
Did Colorful Culture Media pay you too?

837
00:42:39,140 --> 00:42:41,100
Ms. Mei, money is the last thing I lack.

838
00:42:41,340 --> 00:42:42,460
My father is far wealthier

839
00:42:42,460 --> 00:42:43,822
than Colorful Culture Media.

840
00:42:44,020 --> 00:42:46,300
If you said
she was planted here by He Han,

841
00:42:46,300 --> 00:42:47,220
I'd believe that more.

842
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:50,377
But Zhao Lanxin and Ling Yikai...

843
00:42:51,140 --> 00:42:51,780
That's unlikely.

844
00:42:53,220 --> 00:42:53,900
Then who is it?

845
00:42:54,620 --> 00:42:55,100
Mantou?

846
00:42:56,060 --> 00:42:56,780
Fragile?

847
00:42:57,460 --> 00:42:58,300
Or Naobaijin?

848
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

849
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

850
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

851
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

852
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

853
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

854
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

855
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

856
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

857
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

858
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

859
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

860
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

861
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

862
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

863
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

864
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

865
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

866
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

867
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

868
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

869
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

870
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

871
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

872
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

873
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

874
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

875
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

876
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

877
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

878
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

879
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

880
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

881
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

882
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

883
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

884
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
